stylometry: Optimization is when a model tries to "optimize" or achieve the prime goal, whether that is minimizing cost or maximizing profit. In optimization there is the objective function, which is what you are trying to minimize or maximize (target cell), decision variables, which in excel are called changing cells meaning that they are what can change that effects your optimization, and finally constraints which are the limits with which you are held between. An example of optimization is if I have a business of making chairs. There is a set cost and variable cost to each chair I make. Also, I only have a certain amount of wood that I can use, and different types of wood. I want to maximize my profit. My profit would be my objective, or target cell, my changing cell or decision variables are the number of chairs to make, and my constraints would be how much wood I have available to me.
